{"id": "a2f47d18ecdebd56fdfb11846e60d5c7", "ts": "1775586780.000000", "text": "I've come across something troubling. While running hash comparisons on all stipend receipt files in Airtable, I found two records with identical SHA-256 hashes. Kevin Tran (Vectral) and Andre Washington (Mosaic) both submitted the same $89 receipt PDF from TechComfort Supply for an ergonomic keyboard. These are two different individuals from separate companies, which seems unlikely to be a coincidence.

Additionally, there's a third case to highlight: Jordan Ekwueme (BrightLoop) submitted a $45 monitor stand receipt from TechComfort Supply. Although the hash is different, the PDF /Creator metadata and /Template ID are the same as those in the Tran/Washington receipts — they both used the same receipt generation template (TC-RECEIPT-STD-041). The structural metadata fingerprint aligns as well.

This means there are three questionable receipts from three different clients. I need to bring this to Marcus's attention.", "type": "message", "bot_id": null, "subtype": "null", "user_id": "moveops_dmitri_volkov", "edited_ts": null, "permalink": null, "channel_id": "C003", "created_at": "2026-04-07T18:33:00+00:00", "files_json": "[]", "edited_user": null, "reply_count": 0, "latest_reply": "null", "client_msg_id": "scenario_scenario_eea102a1_audit_discovery_11", "metadata_json": "{}", "reactions_json": "[{"name": "eyes", "users": ["moveops_samira_tariq"], "count": 1}]", "attachments_json": "[]", "thread_parent_id": null, "thread_ts_legacy": "1773157200.000000", "reply_users_count": 0, "is_activity_message": false}

{"id": "d04986014a5554a433d89503a5238164", "ts": "1775598420.000000", "text": "Great job identifying this, Dmitri. The cross-client gap is especially alarming — it indicates that the duplicate vector isn't merely a theoretical issue, but something that can be exploited in practice.

I agree that implementing a hash-based deduplication stage before CategoryMatcher is the best course of action. Regarding the PDF metadata comparison, we should consider whether we want only exact matches or if a similarity threshold would suffice — template IDs are a strong indicator, but we may encounter slight differences in generator versions among legitimate receipts from the same vendor.

